5:
Hello, we're here with a delivery from
the Guild.
9:
Oh my, welcome. Hehe, the Guild
certainly is quick. I really appreciate
it.
19:
Oh, that? I made that with the
materials you all oh so graciously
brought last time. What do you think?
23: It would look good on Light.
29:
Me?! B-but that pattern... How
garish... and cutesy...
34:
Oh dear, I happen to agree with
Stella though. It would be adorable
on you. Would you like to try it on?
40:
I-I will have to pass... Besides, it
seems too big for me. Yes, that's it!
Far too big!
45:
Welcome. What sort of apparel are
you looking for today?
48: O-oh, no, I just... I... Urgh...
50:
I-I'm sorry, I seem to have come to
the wrong store... Just forget I was
here...
54:
There's no need to be embarrassed,
sir. Perhaps you would like to chat
for a moment?
60:
So you need an outfit for your
golden wedding anniversary...
65:
Oh, what a wonderous occasion. It's
no wonder you want everything to
go well.
67:
Yes... My wife has put a lot of effort
into this. She's already picked out
her dress...
68:
On the other hand, I'm clueless
when it comes to fancy clothes... I
don't know what to do...
70: Well, what's your normal style like?
75:
Perhaps it would be easier to
coordinate with your wife's attire.
80:
Pardon me, but did you perhaps
work at sea in the past?
83:
I-indeed I did. I was often away at
sea for long periods of time... How
did you know?
85:
I just noticed your beautifully
suntanned skin and thought that
might be the case.
87:
I see... Well, I've since retired and
now live with my wife and son. We
even ended up moving to Palpebra.
89:
Heh, how nostalgic. The roar of the
ocean, the sandy beach... I even
proposed there...
91:
Ah, m-my apologies. It seems this
old man is rambling again.
95:
Not at all. Quite the opposite
actually. That all sounds lovely.
98:
...Sir, would it be possible for me to
make your outfit?
103:
Oh my! Dear, where did you get that
outfit?
105:
I-I had it tailor-made. I just, um... felt
like it, you know?
107:
Hehe, well, you look very handsome.
It reminds me of your old work
uniform...
110:
I see now. You based his clothing off
of his memories...
113:
That's correct. After hearing his
story, I could see him rushing home
to see his wife without changing out
of his uniform.
116:
So... I'm sure the wife has plenty of
fond memories of that uniform as
well...
121:
It looks like you were spot-on there. I
mean... Look at them.
129:
Hehe... And I'm happiest when my
clients are happy.
131:
Seeing their smiles makes me glad I
do what I do.
135:
Well then, I suppose it's time for me
to move on to my next project!
140:
Already?! I think you should take a
break...
144:
I understand you're a popular tailor,
but all of that will be meaningless if
you end up wearing yourself out.
148:
Don't worry about me. I make sure to
rest when I need it!
150:
Besides... I want to make outfits for
all of you next.
154:
Th-that would be great, but... Are
you sure?
159:
Of course! Leave it to me. My clothes
will bring you joy on an entirely
different level!
171:
Agreed. Although... Please refrain
from making my outfit too cutesy...
